				\begin{document}$${I}_{3}^{-}$$\end{document} is reduced to I−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${I}^{-}$$\end{document} more effectively with the P150 CE than the bare PEDOT CE. Moreover, the diffusion coefficient (D) of triiodide on the surface of the CEs can be calculated using the limiting diffusion current density (Jlim), which is extracted from the diffusion zone of the Tafel plot using the following equation:D=Jliml2FnC\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
